<p>=======<wbr />=======<wbr />=======<wbr />=======<wbr />=======<wbr />======<br />
Title: Unintentional role granting with Keystone LDAP backend<br />
Reporter: The IBM OpenStack test team<br />
Products: Keystone<br />
Affects: Grizzly, Havana</p>
<p>Description:<br />
The IBM OpenStack test team reported a vulnerability in role change code within the Keystone LDAP backend. When a role on a tenant is removed from a user, and that user doesn&#x27;t have that role on the tenant, then the user may actually be granted the role on the tenant. A user could use social engineering and leverage that vulnerability to get extra roles granted, or may accidentally be granted extra roles. Only Keystone setups using a LDAP backend are affected.<br />
=======<wbr />=======<wbr />=======<wbr />=======<wbr />=======<wbr />======</p></div>
    
    
    
